abstract: Hillary Clinton is not earning same support among Hispanics, who account for nearly one in five Florida voters, as Pres Obama did in 2012, boosting Donald Trump's chances of winning state; many believe Florida is bellweather for rest of nation and may presage troubles elsewhere.

headline.print_headline: Clinton Struggles in Florida, Despite Supposed Advantages
headline.main: Hillary Clinton Struggles to Gain Traction in Florida, Despite Spending

snippet: Recent polls show Mrs. Clinton is not earning the same support of Hispanics, young people or white voters as President Obama did in 2012, which offers Donald J. Trump an opening....
lead_paragraph: Recent polls show Mrs. Clinton is not earning the same support of Hispanics, young people or white voters as President Obama did in 2012, which offers Donald J. Trump an opening.
